# Public docs directory (`/{locale}/ask-docs`)

## Surface contract

- **Public, no auth gate.** `proxy.ts` matcher excludes this surface from the session cookie check.
- **Locale-first.** All URLs are `/{locale}/ask-docs/…` via `localePrefix: "always"`. Never emit a bare `/ask-docs/…` URL from server code — use `toLocalePath(locale, "/ask-docs/…")`.
- **Static by default.** Pages use `export const dynamic = "force-static"`. Do not add dynamic data fetching to docs pages.
- **No ERP data.** Docs pages and components must not import from `#features/*`, `#lib/auth`, or any server-only ERP module.

## Fumadocs MDX config (`source.config.ts`)

`defineDocs` extends `pageSchema` for Afenda frontmatter and enables link-reference postprocessing:

```ts
import { metaSchema, pageSchema } from "fumadocs-core/source/schema"
import { z } from "zod"

export const docs = defineDocs({
  dir: "content/ask-docs",
  docs: {
    async: true,
    schema: pageSchema.extend({ /* audience, status, lastReviewedAt */ }),
    postprocess: {
      includeProcessedMarkdown: true,
      extractLinkReferences: true,
    },
    async mdxOptions(environment) {
      return applyMdxPreset({ /* remarkNpm, remarkSteps, Twoslash, … */ })(environment)
    },
  },
  meta: { schema: metaSchema },
})

// page.tsx: `const loaded = await page.data.load()` — body, toc, lastModified live on `loaded`.
```

`defineConfig` plugins: `lastModified()`, `jsonSchema({ insert: true })`. Per-collection `async mdxOptions` uses `applyMdxPreset` (`remarkNpm` package-manager persistence, `remarkSteps`, structured search via `remarkStructure`, Shiki + Twoslash). Custom plugins: `remarkMdxMermaid`, `remarkAutoTypeTable`, `remarkTypeScriptToJavaScript`.

`experimentalBuildCache` is intentionally **not** enabled — the cache is never auto-invalidated and requires a manual directory delete. Safe to add only when MDX compilation becomes a measurable CI bottleneck and a cache-bust strategy (e.g. Turborepo `outputs` + `inputs` hash) is in place.

## Source and loader

```ts
// ✅ always scope source to the active locale
import { askDocsSource } from "#lib/ask-docs/source"
const page = askDocsSource.getPage(slug, locale)
const tree = askDocsSource.getPageTree(locale)

// ❌ never import docs collection directly in app/ or components/
import { docs } from "#collections/server"
```

`askDocsSource` is a single Fumadocs `loader()` with `defineI18n` (`en`, `zh-CN`, `vi`, `ms`). Pass locale to `getPage(slug, locale)` and `getPageTree(locale)` — URLs are `/{locale}/ask-docs/...` via Fumadocs i18n (`hideLocale: "never"`).

**Loader plugin wired:** `lucideIconsPlugin()` — converts the `icon` property in MDX frontmatter and `meta.json` to Lucide React elements automatically. Use any [Lucide icon name](https://lucide.dev/icons/) (PascalCase):

```mdx
---
title: Getting Started
icon: BookOpen
---
```

```json
{ "title": "HRM", "icon": "Users", "pages": ["employees", "attendance"] }
```

## Writing MDX content

- Files live under `content/ask-docs/`.
- Every directory needs a `meta.json` to control sidebar order and titles.
- Run `pnpm lint:ask-docs-links` after adding or changing internal links (`[text](/ask-docs/…)`).
- Run `pnpm lint:ask-docs-prose` after substantive MDX edits (markdownlint-cli2; config `.config/markdownlint-ask-docs.jsonc`).
- Run `pnpm lint:ask-docs-quality` after substantive MDX edits (stub strings, Related graph, stable frontmatter).
- Scaffold new pages with `pnpm gen ask-doc` (enforces frontmatter + section skeleton; use `--archetype` when available) or batch via `pnpm ask-docs:scaffold` + `content/ask-docs/scaffold.manifest.json`.
- Before a docs PR: `pnpm ask-docs:preflight` (`validate-manifest` + fixture `scaffold:dry-run` + `ask-docs:check`).
- After substantive edits: `pnpm ask-docs:check` (links + prose + ADQS quality). Compile is automatic on `pnpm dev` / `pnpm build` via Fumadocs — do not add `gen ask-doc` to `prebuild`.
- Preview scaffold: `pnpm ask-docs:validate-manifest` then `pnpm ask-docs:scaffold -- --dry-run` (production manifest) or `pnpm ask-docs:scaffold:dry-run` (fixture).

### ADQS — Ask-Docs Quality Standard (target ≥95% = 47.5/50)

**Mandatory agent workflow:** apply `.agents/skills/adqs/SKILL.md` automatically when authoring or improving `content/ask-docs/**`. Do not invoke `documentation-audit`, `technical-writing`, or Fumadocs skills separately — ADQS composes them:

1. **Phase 1 — Accuracy audit** (`.agents/skills/documentation-audit/`) — grep routes, permissions, audit strings; remove stubs.
2. **Phase 2 — Prose** (`.agents/skills/technical-writing/`, mode `internal-guide`) — Overview → Before you start → workflow → Troubleshooting → Related.
3. **Phase 3 — Gates** — `pnpm lint:ask-docs-links` · `lint:ask-docs-prose` · `lint:ask-docs-quality` · `node scripts/audit-ask-docs-quality.mjs`.

Score each page before merge. Do not ship generator stubs.

| # | Dimension | /10 | 95% requires |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Frontmatter | 10 | `title`, `description` (≥8 chars, not duplicate of first paragraph), `audience`, `status`, contextual Lucide `icon`; `lastReviewedAt` when `status: stable` |
| 2 | Structure | 10 | `Overview` → `Before you start` → workflow → optional `## Troubleshooting` → `Related` |
| 3 | Fumadocs components | 10 | Non-placeholder `<Steps>` (≥3 when workflow exists); ≥1 `<Callout>`; `<Cards>` in `Related`; `<Tabs>` / `<Accordions>` when multi-path or FAQ |
| 4 | Code-verified accuracy | 10 | Paths match App Router; read-only vs mutate correct; step-up and audit match implementation |
| 5 | Link graph | 10 | ≥2 `/ask-docs/…` links; hub + module doc where applicable; passes `lint:ask-docs-links` |
| 6 | LLM / search | 10 | No stub comments; clear `##` headings; no “relevant workspace” on `audience: employee` portal pages |

**Gold patterns:** `content/ask-docs/getting-started/quick-start.mdx` (nested `<Step>` + in-step `<Callout>`), `content/ask-docs/hrm/documents.mdx` (audit Callout + tables), `content/ask-docs/portals/employee.mdx` (hub).

**Archetypes:** `workflow` · `readonly` · `stepup` · `hub` — pass to `pnpm gen ask-doc --archetype …` when scaffolding.
- Internal links in MDX must use the `/ask-docs/…` authoring form (no locale prefix). The link validator expands them to `/{locale}/ask-docs/…` automatically.
- **Inline code syntax highlighting:** append `{:lang}` to inline code — e.g. `` `const x = 1{:ts}` `` or `` `SELECT *{:sql}` ``. Plain inline code without the suffix renders as-is (backward-compatible).

```mdx
<!-- ✅ authoring form -->
[Getting started](/ask-docs/getting-started)

<!-- ❌ never include a locale prefix in MDX links -->
[Getting started](/en/ask-docs/getting-started)
```

## OG images

- Helper: `getAskDocsOgImagePath(locale, slugs)` from `#lib/ask-docs/og.shared`.
- Endpoint: `app/og/ask-docs/[locale]/[...slug]/route.tsx` — `next/og` `ImageResponse`, `revalidate = false`.
- The `/og` path segment is excluded from the `proxy.ts` intl matcher so next-intl never rewrites it.
- Trailing segment is `image.png` (`ASK_DOCS_OG_IMAGE_FILENAME`).
- `generateMetadata` in `page.tsx` wires `openGraph.images` and `twitter.images` to this path.

## Search

- Endpoint: `app/api/ask-docs-search/route.ts` — Fumadocs Orama via `createFromSource(askDocsSource, { localeMap })`. Accepts `?locale=`.
- Do not add `app/api/search/` — duplicate route removed. Do not add ERP search on ask-docs.

## Public Lynx (Ask AI)

- UI: `#components2/ai/search` — `AISearch`, `AISearchPanel`, `AISearchTrigger` wired in `app/(ask-docs)/[locale]/ask-docs/layout.tsx` (label **Ask Lynx**).
- API: `app/api/chat/route.ts` — Vercel AI SDK `streamText` + flexsearch tool over ask-docs processed markdown. **No** `#features/lynx` import.
- Requires `AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY` locally (or `VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN` on Vercel) and `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_*` for production rate limits. Parse POST via `readPublicLynxChatRequestBody` — not `req.json()`.
- Lint: `pnpm lint:public-lynx-contract` after changes to `app/api/chat`, `components2/ai/search`, or `lib/ask-docs/public-lynx*`.
- Rule: `.cursor/rules/public-lynx.mdc`.

## LLM export endpoints

| Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `app/llms.txt/route.ts` | Plain-text index (all pages, one URL per line) |
| `app/llms-full.txt/route.ts` | Full processed markdown for all pages |
| `app/llms.mdx/ask-docs/[locale]/[[...slug]]/route.ts` | Per-page markdown GET; in-app links use `getAskDocsProcessedMarkdownPath(locale, slug)`; `/{locale}/ask-docs/*.md` rewrites to `/llms.mdx/ask-docs/:locale/...` |

All three use `revalidate = false` and `Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable`.

## Feedback

- `<Feedback onSendAction={submitAskDocsFeedback} />` — client island in `components/feedback/client.tsx`.
- Server Action `submitAskDocsFeedback` lives in `app/(ask-docs)/[locale]/ask-docs/[[...slug]]/actions.ts`.
- Log via `rootLogger.info` from `#lib/logger.server`. Never `console.log`.
- No DB writes for feedback yet — logging only. Add a DB write when a feedback table is added to `lib/db/schema.ts`.

## Fumadocs UI wiring

### Theme
`globals.css` already imports `fumadocs-ui/css/shadcn.css` + `fumadocs-ui/css/preset.css`. The `shadcn` preset inherits the project's existing design tokens rather than introducing a separate neutral palette. No changes needed.

### `RootProvider`
Placed at `app/(ask-docs)/[locale]/ask-docs/layout.tsx` (scoped to the docs surface, not the app root). Provides search dialog context (`/api/ask-docs-search`). Theme is inherited from the main app shell on `/ask-docs` unless overridden.

**`search.links`** — Quick-links shown when the search dialog is empty. Wired to the top-level sections (when used):
```tsx
<RootProvider search={{ links: [
  ["Getting Started", toLocalePath(locale, "/ask-docs/getting-started")],
  ["HRM", toLocalePath(locale, "/ask-docs/hrm")],
  // ...
] }}>
```
Update `ask-docs/layout.tsx` whenever a new top-level section is added to `content/ask-docs/`.

### `DocsLayout`
`askDocsBaseLayoutOptions(locale)` in `app/(ask-docs)/[locale]/ask-docs/_lib/layout-options.ts` owns notebook chrome for this surface. Extend there — never inline layout config in `layout.tsx`. Layout options available:
- `sidebar.prefetch: false` — safe to leave at default (`true`) because docs are `force-static` (served from CDN edge, not serverless functions).
- `sidebar.defaultOpenLevel: 1` — currently set to open the first nesting level by default. ✅
- `tabs` — Root-folder layout tabs; add `"root": true` to a `meta.json` when tab navigation is needed.
- `sidebar.banner` — Optional banner inside the sidebar (e.g. version selector, CTA).

### `DocsPage` — auto-rendered slots
`DocsPage` automatically renders:
- **Breadcrumb** — top-of-page path navigation (can be disabled with `breadcrumb={{ enabled: false }}`)
- **Footer** — prev/next page navigation (can be disabled with `footer={{ enabled: false }}`)
- **Table of Contents** — from `toc={page.data.toc}` (can be disabled with `tableOfContent={{ enabled: false }}`)

No explicit slot components needed for standard usage. The `slots` prop and `slots/` exports from `fumadocs-ui/layouts/docs/page/slots/*` are only for deep custom replacements.

### `PageLastUpdate`
Use the official `PageLastUpdate` component from `fumadocs-ui/layouts/notebook/page` (same layout family as `DocsPage` on this surface):
```tsx
import { PageLastUpdate } from "fumadocs-ui/layouts/notebook/page"
{page.data.lastModified && <PageLastUpdate date={page.data.lastModified} />}
```

### MDX components — `defaultMdxComponents` inventory
`defaultMdxComponents` from `fumadocs-ui/mdx` already provides:

| Key | Component | Source |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `pre` | `CodeBlock` + `Pre` | Built-in code block with copy button |
| `Card`, `Cards` | Card layout | For linked section cards |
| `Callout`, `CalloutContainer`, `CalloutTitle`, `CalloutDescription` | Callout | Info / warning / error / tip boxes |
| `a` | `Link` | Locale-aware links (overridden by `createRelativeLink`) |
| `img` | Sized image | Overridden by `ImageZoom` in `app/(ask-docs)/.../_components/mdx.tsx` |
| `h1`–`h6` | `Heading` | With automatic anchor IDs |
| `table` | `Table` | Overflow-safe table wrapper |
| `CodeBlockTab`, `CodeBlockTabs`, etc. | Tab groups | For `tab="..."` code fence syntax |

**No need to import or re-register these** — they arrive via `...defaultMdxComponents` spread.

**`DocsCategory` — NOT available in fumadocs-ui v16.** The Fumadocs docs site uses its own custom implementation; it is not exported from the package. Build a custom category index component if section overview cards are needed on `index.mdx` pages.

### `--fd-layout-width`
Default is `97rem` (very wide). Can be scoped to the ask-docs surface via globals.css:
```css
/* Scope this inside an .ask-docs-surface selector or add to :root only if docs is the main surface */
:root { --fd-layout-width: 80rem; }
```
Defer until the layout width becomes a design complaint; it does not affect functionality.

## Components

- `app/(ask-docs)/[locale]/ask-docs/_components/mdx.tsx` — `useMDXComponents`: vanilla Fumadocs shelf. Add new MDX components here only.
- **Notebook layout exports** — `app/(ask-docs)/[locale]/ask-docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx` imports `MarkdownCopyButton`, `ViewOptionsPopover`, `DocsPage`, etc. from `fumadocs-ui/layouts/notebook/page` (Fumadocs-styled copy / view-as-markdown / GitHub when `NEXT_PUBLIC_ASK_DOCS_GITHUB_URL` is set via `getAskDocsGithubUrl`). Optional **Links on this page** uses `page.data.extractedReferences` from `extractLinkReferences` postprocess.
- These patterns are for the public docs surface only. Do not import notebook layout pieces from ERP pages.

## TypeScript type tables

Two authoring modes are available — both are fully wired:

| Mode | MDX syntax | Path is relative to… | When to use |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Build-time** (`remarkAutoTypeTable`) | `<auto-type-table path="./types.ts" name="MyProps" />` | The MDX file itself | Preferred. Evaluated at `next build`; fastest. |
| **RSC** (`AutoTypeTable`) | `<AutoTypeTable path="lib/features/x/types.ts" name="MyType" />` | Project root (`cwd`) | For live type references where MDX-relative paths are inconvenient. |

Both require `TypeTable` from `fumadocs-ui/components/type-table` (already registered).

**TSDoc annotations** supported in either mode:

| Annotation | Effect |
| --- | --- |
| `@internal` | Hide the field from the table |
| `@remarks \`alias\` description` | Show `alias` instead of the raw TS type |
| `@fumadocsType \`name\`` | Override the displayed type name |
| `@fumadocsHref #anchor` | Link the field to another type table anchor |

## Layout options

`askDocsBaseLayoutOptions(locale)` in `app/(ask-docs)/[locale]/ask-docs/_lib/layout-options.ts` returns `DocsLayoutProps`. Extend this function for nav links, sidebar config changes, or i18n options — do not inline layout config in `layout.tsx`.

## Split trigger

Extract to a standalone Fumadocs Next.js app (e.g. `docs.afenda.com`) when **any** of:
- `content/ask-docs/` exceeds ~50 MDX files and authoring velocity requires a CMS.
- A non-engineering team needs to publish without a Next.js deploy.
- The Fumadocs surface needs a different design system or theming from the main app.

Until then, keep co-located. The surface is already statically generated and adds negligible build cost.

## Content source

The current content source is **Fumadocs MDX** (`fumadocs-mdx`): bundler-based, build-time compilation, full import/export support, build-time image optimisation.

Do **not** migrate to an alternative content source without a named trigger:

| Alternative | Migration trigger | Why not now |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **`@fumadocs/local-md`** | Content must update without a redeploy AND imports/image-opt can be dropped | Bundleless runtime — loses build-time image optimisation and MDX import/export. All our MDX components (`TypeTable`, `Mermaid`, `ImageZoom`) depend on the bundler pass. |
| **`@fumadocs/mdx-remote`** | Content is fetched from a remote API at runtime, not committed to the repo | Same tradeoffs as local-md. No upside while content lives in `content/ask-docs/`. |
| **`@fumadocs/sanity`** | A Sanity project and studio exist AND non-engineering authors need a CMS UI | Requires full Sanity infra (project, studio, schema types, API keys). No current infrastructure. |
| **Custom Loader API** (`fumadocs-core/source`) | A content source exists that has no Fumadocs adapter | Already used — `lib/ask-docs/source.ts` calls `loader()`. No further custom implementation needed unless pulling from a novel source. |

## Deferred integrations

Do **not** add these without a named requirement:

| Integration | When to add |
| --- | --- |
| `fumadocs-openapi` | An OpenAPI spec file exists and API reference docs are needed |
| `@fumadocs/story` | Component `.story.tsx` files exist and interactive props are needed in MDX |
| Takumi (`@takumi-rs/image-response`) | OG image render time is a measurable bottleneck (unlikely for static gen) |
| Notebook layout (`fumadocs-ui/layouts/notebook`) | More compact layout without a persistent sidebar; requires updating the page import from `…/docs/page` to `…/notebook/page`. Defer until a compact mode is explicitly requested. |
| `Banner` component (`fumadocs-ui/components/banner`) | Site-wide announcement needed. Place at the top of the root layout inside the `<body>`. Supports `variant="rainbow"`, `id` for dismissal persistence. |

## Fumadocs CLI (`@fumadocs/cli`)

Config: `cli.json` at repo root — already initialised. Do not re-run `pnpm dlx @fumadocs/cli` (init only).

| Command | Purpose | When to run |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `pnpm dlx @fumadocs/cli add <name>` | Install an ejectable Fumadocs component into `components/` | When you need a customisable copy of a component the package ships (e.g. `banner`, `files`). Check Fumadocs GitHub for available names. |
| `pnpm dlx @fumadocs/cli tree ./dir ./output.tsx` | Generate `<Files>/<Folder>/<File>` JSX from a real directory | For MDX content that documents a directory structure. Output can be `.tsx` (paste inline) or `.mdx` (import). |
| `pnpm dlx @fumadocs/cli customize` | Eject a Fumadocs layout component into `layouts/` for deep customisation | Defer — only when `DocsLayout` props are insufficient and layout source must be modified. |

**`tree` output components** (`File`, `Folder`, `Files`) are registered in `app/(ask-docs)/.../_components/mdx.tsx` and available in all MDX files:

```mdx
<Files>
  <Folder name="app" defaultOpen>
    <File name="layout.tsx" />
    <File name="page.tsx" />
  </Folder>
  <File name="package.json" />
</Files>
```

## Lint gates

```bash
pnpm ask-docs:preflight       # validate manifest + fixture dry-run + quality (pre-PR)
pnpm ask-docs:check           # links + prose + quality (after content edits)
pnpm ask-docs:validate-manifest
pnpm ask-docs:scaffold -- --dry-run
pnpm ask-docs:scaffold:dry-run
pnpm ask-docs:scaffold        # batch gen from scaffold.manifest.json (on demand)
pnpm lint:ask-docs-links      # internal URLs in MDX
pnpm lint:ask-docs-prose      # markdownlint-cli2
pnpm lint:ask-docs-quality    # ADQS stubs, Related graph, frontmatter (ADR-0027)
pnpm audit:ask-docs-quality   # optional corpus tier report → .artifacts/ask-docs-quality-audit.txt
pnpm exec eslint --max-warnings=0 "app/(ask-docs)" app/og/ask-docs app/api/ask-docs-search app/api/chat components2/ai/search.tsx components2/ask-docs-mermaid.tsx lib/ask-docs source.config.ts scripts/ask-docs-check-gate.mjs scripts/ask-docs-scaffold-from-manifest.mjs scripts/lib/ask-docs-scaffold-manifest.shared.mjs
pnpm typecheck
```

